		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(125750927, 'Examinations covered material from the audio and video lectures, as well as the book very fairly. They were just the right amount of difficulty to where if you knew where to look in the book and had listened to the lectures, then you would do very well on the exams and quizzes. There were technical difficulties with the Blackboard systems several times throughout the course, but from the class standpoint, the exams were still very good for an online class.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(125750928, 'Really, nothing. There were times when the instructor was late in posting links for certain downloads that were needed for the assignments, but the independence he gave the class seemed the perfect mix of freedom and self-learning. It challenged the mind and really made the class one of the best I''ve ever had here at Weber.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(124662572, 'It would have been nice if there was a current grade average page on the website to see where we stood, grade-wise, throughout the semester. However, I don''t know if that''s possible as my other class was having trouble with her grade average using the Canvas website.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(125750929, 'I particularly liked the fluency of the online course and the clear rubric and outline you could follow. You could move at your own pace and change things up on how you did them for certain assignments/sections, and the material challenged your thinking very well. The answer was also always there, no matter what, either in the audio lectures, the video lectures, or the book, as well as through the online discussion board and emailing system. Overall, I think the course was extremely balanced, the discussions good, the independence through awesome lectures superb, and the professor very funny and extremely supportive throughout the semester. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(124662573, 'My favorite part of the course was the online lectures. I wish Mr. Hilton would teach more CS classes with Weber so I could take all my future classes with him. I received my AA in IT from Univ of Phoenix and have taken multiple computer-related classes online. None of the teachers seemed to "teach" but only handed assignments from the required reading of the textbooks. It seemed they were only hired because of their degrees and professional work experience rather than their teaching skills.

Mr. Hilton is by far the best CS teacher I''ve ever had. I can also compare him with a C++ class that I registered for this same semester with a different online professor. I ended up dropping the other course, not because of the material, but because of the teacher. There are some teachers, like Mr. Hilton, that make learning fun and encourage students to do their best. I''ve run into too many other teachers that have forgotten that the enthusiasm they have for the subject matter greatly affects the learning experience of the student. A BS in CS can be intimidating, but with teachers like Mr. Hilton, he takes the fear factor out and uses encouragement and a "can do" attitude that his students can feed from to ultimately reach their goals.');
	
