		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(157835336, 'I remember sitting in one of our meeting times we were discussing elevation levels and floor joist. That information I found extremely helpful I just wish it had been given to me day one. This class CANNOT be online. Completing the project was very difficult I had a lot of questions and felt they would have all been answered in a lecture style course. 

This class was most definitely a learning experience for all of us. I did complain a lot, especially about one of my partners who did absolutely nothing and when he would check up on the house all he would do is critique what I hadn''t done instead of applauding me for my work. It hurt my feelings because I had spent hours trying to get everything to work out properly. He would also proceed to tell me how stressed he was about this project which was CRAP because he hadn''t done a single thing. I can count on one hand all the things he did to contribute to our group. Anyway, I thought this was the complain about your partner section. If I had a do over I would have chosen a different partner. 

At the end of the day I don''t feel like this project was a total bust and I want you to realize that. I learned more about Revit in this class than in any of the others. Having the freedom to do what I wanted instead of following steps from a book gave me more ambition to complete the project. I wanted to win. I wanted to have the best design. I wanted to please the client. I wanted to prove myself to my partner ^ who thought he was a big shot because he worked in the industry (using Revit.) The desire to achieve all my goals from this project gave me the motivation to learn as much about Revit as I possibly could. The only thing that held me back was the time. I had to restart my project several times because things weren''t working out, or we changed the wall type, etc. Because of this I didn''t have time to get renderings of the house done. Now I could possibly lose the competition because of it. Long story short and I know you realize this is that this class CANNOT be taught online. I feel like I wouldn''t of had to start over several times if we had meant as a class. ');
	
