		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(171287452, 'This was--hands down--the most difficult class I have even taken. The scope of material presented in this class is extreme, especially considering this is only a 2000-level class. If the expectation is to learn or master the material in the time allotted, then I think the class should be broken into two separate semesters so this can be achieved. The material is simply overwhelming, especially to a student like myself who simply needed an anatomy or physiology class to complete general ed requirements. I know I have learned things from this class--the professor was excellent and great about communicating with all of us--and I could share general ideas of physiology with anyone put before me to discuss them, but the specificity of the exam questions were beyond the scope of my capabilities. As confident as I was going into each exam, I still was shocked when I saw my grade at the end of each one. Again, if we are expected to master this subject--and it seems like maybe some of the students were delving further into human sciences and would need to do just that--then I think splitting this class up into two semesters would afford any future students the chance to do so and they could keep up with the pace. ');
	
