		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178178646, 'The instructor is incredibly enthusiastic and made learning this subject fun and manageable, especially being that the course was taught online. The materials she posted for each module was incredibly helpful and I never had questions about what was expected of me each week. I took this course from a different instructor last year and I was not interested and struggled to keep up the whole semester. Michelle Skopec made the course information relatable and helped with life application. I would recommend this class and instructor to anyone in this field.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178312610, 'It was a challenging class but it was good');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178597461, 'This is the only class that I took at Weber State since I am a USU student.  I loved the set up of the class and that the lectures were recorded in the lecture hall.  Sometimes not being able to see what was being written on the board was frustrating but hearing live questions and answers outweighed this. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178187679, 'I loved that Jeremy was so passionate about the course and made it fun to learn about green building.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(177719946, 'I thought the class was done well. There were issues of course with the professor switching out halfway through the semester, but that isn''t anything that could have been avoided. Professor Strickland did a great job taking over after Professor Triplett''s absence.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178036763, 'I learned so much in this course. I learned about so many different perspective that I hadn''t thought about before. As educators we need to be able to see things from all perspectives and be open to ideas. Dr Garcia tried to help us know how to look at things this way.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178042236, 'One thing that I might change is to add another novel to the overall lesson plan. It is interesting to see how all the different elements, such as la curanderas and la Llorona, come into play in the different stories. It might be fun if there was a way to add a third novel to the curriculum.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178036762, 'Dr Garcia was very professional. He is one of the best professors that I have had the opportunity to have a class from at Weber State. I cannot think of anything for him to improve.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178187680, 'I think that this course is incredible the way it is. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178042235, 'I liked the overall explanation pages provided in each section giving a basic outline on the different subjects, such as the information outline on the curanderas in la curanderas section. It made it easier to understand the different view points presented in the readings of each section. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178469382, 'Slow down a bit and find a good resource book or manual for the course.  I started out ok, but once I started to fall behind, I feel like I got left in the dust and couldn''t catch up.  A lot of it is that we would talk about something in class and I feel like we were expected to have it memorized.  If not we could go back and watch videos, but that was very helpful, but very time consuming, so a book or manual would have been much  quicker to look something up in.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178187128, 'Dr. Garcia did a great job at establishing open lines for communicating in class.  We covered a number of sensitive topics, but I never felt I couldn''t state my opinion even if it contradicted Dr. Garcia''s.  He was very open and accepting of my opinion.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178042760, 'I liked building the scaled model and using autocad along with it. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(177824756, 'I became more familiar with MLA citations, and the construction of a collegiate level research essay.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178347155, 'I did like how my questions were answered fast and time was spend answering questions');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(177722417, 'Nothing really. This professor was excellent at keeping me on track throughout the whole semester. She would e mail us weekly reminding us of our assignments for the week. I also really liked how she would tell us what chapters to read for the week, and then make us answer some questions from the chapter(s). This class was a lot of work... But that''s college for ya. I really wish more professors were like this one. All of these things were of great value.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178352489, 'It gave great info on green practices. The instructor did a good job of showing us how important going green was.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178481102, 'I loved all the in class examples, they really helped me to learn the material.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178042761, 'The ebook and other resources didn''t always contain the necessary information to answer the module questions. Also the schedule and assignment dates were off in canvas. Other than that the course was great.  ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178178429, 'How everything tied together and the creative ways some concepts were explained.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178178913, 'I loved everything about this course. It was really hard for me, but I was able to overcome the material with a strong work-ethic. I learned so much in this class. I feel it really helped me prepare myself for the real world. Coming into the class, I didn''t feel confident about my programming skills. after the first three assignments, I felt I could go back and re-write every single 1410 assignment confidently. I also liked how much Brad cared that students understood the material. He often went extraordinarily out of his way to make sure that each student understood all of the material well enough to complete the assignments. He also made the learning environment fun by expressing his inner nerd and using examples from entertainment to effectively teach material.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178513541, 'This course was definitely a challenge for me, but I feel like I am coming away with a good understanding of data structures and more refined programming skills. I like the challenge and the way the course has refined and developed my skills.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178347156, 'I think that rather than creating a house with different designs that you should have each class member create the same model in auto cad similar to the 2000 class with the law office building. It would help me use and understand auto cad as well as helping me know what the project is suppose to look right other than trying to guess on certain things.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178051163, 'I took this class online which is where I have taken the majority of my CS classes and I have discovered that the instructor makes or breaks the learning experience.  Professor Peterson is the most online friendly professor I have taken a course from.  He goes out of his way to give online students an opportunity to actively participate in the course and was always sure to provide any help on a subject I didn''t understand.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178208572, 'The teacher lectures');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178469383, 'He was a very good instructor that really made the class very interesting. He was funny and made the class a very fun learning environment.  ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178197071, 'The clarity of the lectures. Brad did a great job of keeping topic in his lectures very clear. Even when points intermingled he still kept them clear. He has a huge knowledge of what he teaches. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178199146, 'The assignments were a great learning tool.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178178430, 'none');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178178914, 'The one thing I didn''t like much were the participation quizzes. I don''t find it necessary to have to require that of students. If they want to not pay attention and fail, that''s their own business. However, each lecture was made available to any student at literally any time. So there''s no reason or excuse a student couldn''t complete them unless they deliberately chose not to do it. And in my case, it didn''t really matter anyway, since I actively participated in each and every lecture for my class time. I easily completed them the second they were given. I do understand why it was instilled, though.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178632460, 'N/A');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178352490, 'I didn''t like the LEED GA practice quizes. I read the material but still felt like I was guessing on most of the questions.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178178915, 'Brad Peterson is literally the best professor I''ve ever had at Weber State, and I''ve been attending classes continuously since fall of 2008. He is incredibly knowledgeable in the Computer Science field, and he is incredibly generous and helpful with that knowledge. Whatever happens in the future with this University, he is to stay until the end of time. He''s greatly increasing the quality of Computer Science graduates, and therefore you should greatly increase his salary. (or something nice like that. Seriously.)');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178087603, 'I like your teaching method. Makes things easy to understand. I liked having the lectures available online. Being able to ask you questions via g+ was nice although I can see that being annoying for you.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178513542, 'I can''t think of any improvements for this course. The assignments were reasonable and practical. The lectures were clear and logical. I didn''t feel like I was wasting my time in this course. No suggestions for improvement.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178051165, 'Great course, CS 2420 is very complicated material and I wouldn''t recommend anyone take it online from anyone other than Professor Peterson.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178051164, 'My only complaint is that a fully functioning program that is two hours late should not get a lower grade than a non-fully functioning program that is on time :).  But the syllabus states clearly that this is the policy, I just don''t like the policy :).');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178513543, 'Great class. The instructor taught the subject well and was available for extra instruction/help. ');
	
