		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178399923, 'Peterson''s classes were always fun, and he took as much time as needed to ensure that the concepts were learned. Posting all the lectures online was extremely useful when wanting to review materials.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178399922, 'I would have liked to see actual code on some of the concepts discussed, the ones that did not have a related homework project associated with them. I felt a few things near the end were more complex than earlier ones and had less time devoted to them; this could be purely because I am more interested in graphs and pathing algorithms than sorting ones though.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178395618, 'More study guides or some material that allows us to review what was gone over the week prior, instead of just watching the lecture again online.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178239815, 'I like the material, it made me think a lot about the different products/code I use everyday. I usually code in higher languages for work, but this course taught me that I really could code everything I need to in C++ effectively and the language itself would be useful to learn. I feel like C++ is now a good thing to know and learn, rather than a language I have to deal with to get my degree.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178399921, 'I learned how to use a lot of things within C++ that I felt I didn''t have a great understanding of from my 1410 class.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178089268, 'I wouldn''t change anything - Kim''s course was great!');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178395619, 'Great instructor.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178242685, 'The professor was really awesome. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178574320, 'Aside from reading assignments, we only had two assignments during the course.  One was the presentation on the chapter in the book that we had assigned.  The second was a paper.  I believe that including a short writing assignment in response to the reading would be beneficial.  More students would do the reading if there were some kind of assignment attached to it that was going to be graded.  Also, the one large paper was a bit higher level than we were expecting.  I like the idea of writing a paper connected to the reading assignments but this one felt like it was geared toward graduate level rather than undergrad level.  While I appreciate the faith that we can do that level of work as seniors, with the rest of the education block expectations and assignments it felt like too much.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178232951, 'TEST PREP, the test are hard and are covered on material that is skimmed over in class.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178742852, 'I valued the required book They Say I Say and the teachers use of it for our assignments. I feel like I went from being a total English noob to having some respectable skills. I always got great feedback on my papers and essays and I think it felt motivating for me to keep on going when I felt like someone has my college success in mind.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178906548, 'She is a good instructor and is always willing to answer any questions I have, either by email or in person during office hours. She instructs everything well, and is very fair on what she tests. She is definitely one of the better instructors in the Zoology department.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178089267, 'Toward the beginning of class, several students were struggling with a specific concept. Kim set up an online group Q & A and we were all able to log into the discussion where Kim went over some powerpoint slides and worked on some Q&A with us until we had a better understanding of the material. I thought it was great tht she took time out of her schedule to help us out.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178512240, 'I can''t think of any, this class surpassed most others by a landslide in making sure everyone understood the material and also being able to sit through a 2 hour lecture and still have a good time.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(178906678, 'Great online lab. Not difficult and teaches you what you need to know for the class. Just time consuming, but being able to do it at home is definitely better than having to drive up to WSU to do the same thing.');
	
