		VALUES(179207140, 'Great learning about hoarding!');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(179005782, 'Great teacher! I hope to take another class from her.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(179578178, 'Dr. Skopec seems to really favor the students that do exceptionally well in her class and well the others are just mere faces to her.  So when people that don''t do amazing in her class ask he questions she gives them very short blunt answers whereas if an exceptional student asks she will go above and beyond to answer their question.  Another HUGE issue I have with her is her grading.  There were assignments that she  made sound like they were for fun and that you will get full points on them all long as you do them and that was not the case so she makes assignments seem to be what they really are not.  Overall I liked her as a person but this class and her were no good.  Probably my least favorite class that I have taken up at this University.  ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(179805168, 'One of the best labs I have had here at Weber State. Although the lab reports were very very time consuming I am thankful that I have this added skill. This skill was used in a variety of my other classes as well. 

Thanks for making efficient use of our lab time. I hate it when professors seem not to care about my time which was not at all the case in this lab.

Thanks for a wonderful semester!');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(179805244, 'Dr. Skopec has a very wonderful sense of humor that makes class very interesting and entertaining. As someone who is sincerely interested in her subject material, she does a very good job of engaging students, asking questions, and getting to know each student on a name-name basis. This was very effective in motivating me to study and do well in her class.

I have to be honest, this is hands down the most organized class I have ever had! Thank you!!!! You are a wonderful professor.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(179407109, 'Sometimes it felt like there was too much material being covered but overall very informative. One of the best professors I have had. ');
	
