		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(186657848, 'You need to be more direct and specific. I''m okay with you being relaxed, however we were often confused about if we should be reading on days class was cancelled or not.

I thrived in this class. However, my classmates had trouble with why we were learning this ''stuff.'' I think more an introduction about classroom issues due to identity, then some theory, and then a final project about applying theory to the classroom would be helpful to others.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(186659726, 'I know that critical media aspect is important. However, we really needed indepth knowledge of the SMART board and other classroom technologies. I felt like you weren''t qualified to teach this class. We talked about the SMARTboard for half an hour all semester! I''m expected to be this 21st century teacher and I don''t have the tools I need. We never learned how to recalibrate the SMARTboard, turn it on, how to save ink on word documents etc. 

Spending 4 weeks of class having people present their lessons was a waste of time. We should have been learning about classroom technology. I don''t know how to turn a document camera on. I don''t know the latest and greatest technology in education tools.

This class really failed to provide me what I need to be a successful teacher. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(186670327, 'Maybe some kind of Supplemental Instruction would be useful. I loved the way this class was taught, but a good number of students hated it and had a very hard time learning the new material on their own. I think the way this class was taught is the right way to do it. Its really hard and takes a lot of work, but that''s what college is supposed to be. We need to learn like this or we won''t be prepared for the industry.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(186670328, 'FINALLY A CHALLENGING CLASS. In most of the programming courses I have taken up until this one, we never create a program that goes much further than a fancy "hello world" with a few buttons and calculations, and if we do go further it is not without a great deal of hand-holding. We need more experience setting up an entire project, making applications work with databases and web servers. I learned a lot of basic principles over the years at weber but I didn''t learn much about how to use them in a real situation. Sure I can make a doubly linked list and come up with different algorithms, but what am i going to do with that if i dont know how to create and deploy a project?');
	
