		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190653163, 'Nothing');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190608301, 'Spend a little more time going over how things are set up in code and not just ideas. But if you have to err on one side, you are doing the perfect thing because we''ll remember the concepts better than just memorizing syntax.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(191040328, 'Dr. Skopec has teaching this course down to a science. I was able to effectively learn much more than most other courses due to her organization of lecture videos. Most students don''t learn things after their first exposure to new material. Because Dr. Skopec records her lectures and posts them, I was able to review and re-review until I had truly learned the material. I wish more instructors would adopt her teaching methods. I learned more from her through an online class than many other instructors in the lecture setting. Keep Dr. Skopec teaching ZOOL 2200!!');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190605631, 'A theme song?');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190605632, 'Great instructor - I will keep an eye out for future classes taught by Brad.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190611217, 'I LOVED the lab part of this course! It was fun, and I learned a lot from the labs! ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190869011, 'I feel like the course is already a good one. I enjoy the way that Professor Peterson teaches and this course is no different.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190868275, 'same ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190655605, 'If we could have a few more MTG references that would be great ;)');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190680385, 'It''s a good thing this course is online and attendance is not required, since it would have gone too slowly for me if I hadn''t been able to watch the videos on 2x speed on Youtube. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190655603, 'I like the assignments and the focused learning it created.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190869010, 'I liked the fast paced style that Professor Peterson likes to use in his classes. Developing in this course was fun and working in a group makes it enjoyable.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190677973, 'Challenging real world experience');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190616230, 'Made it an environment where you weren''t afraid to ask questions. Keep it up!!');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190597728, 'Have more instructions and support for assignments.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190677974, 'The whole group getting docked points if one person doesn''t follow through is a little frustrating but so is life, so yeah.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190608406, 'This was a fantastic course. I learned so much about Human Physiology, and Dr. Skopec was the perfect instructor for this course. My expectations for an online class for this subject were far exceeded. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190616231, 'N/A');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190620930, 'Great course, great instructor :)');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190609931, 'None. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190680384, 'None. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190608520, 'I don''t like taking online courses, but I love this professor.  I like the fact that she posts her lectures on canvas, it makes it feel more like a face to face course than an online course. Great class!!');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190609932, 'Brad is a great combination of open-ended or not-so-rigid guidelines (there were few specifics mentioned in what we will accomplish) and pushing us to get a real, dynamic, functional application shipped for an organization. This is one of the two or three best courses I''ve taken in the CS department.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190620929, 'Quicker at grading');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190693213, 'The only thing I would improve is more a departmental thing. Implement general practices from Brad''s style to other CS classes.

Specifically
- Teach concepts not memorization
- Encourage discussion forums (disapprove of handing out answers of course)
- Allow remote attendance through Google+
- Don''t weight the attendance, but heavily weight the actual work
- Record every lecture
- Treat every student equally regardless of grade');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190670506, 'Peterson for President 2016');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190670505, 'Improve any professors that teach this course that aren''t Peterson');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190611057, 'I wish it was made more clear on what needed to be studied for the exams. The study guide did not relate to the exams, and after talking to the TA''s they also agreed that they study guides were a waste of time because they didn''t go with the exams taken ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190608508, 'Loved the lab portion of this course. It helped me learn and remember the subject matter that was taught in the class. Excellent!');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(191022734, 'One of the most enjoyable classes I''ve taken and I hope to be in a class with you again!');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190613163, 'reminder emails for any lab documents that aren''t on a normal day (i.e. collecting data for labs) would be helpful');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(191022733, 'For this class, none. For all other courses, put your lectures online to watch-- it certainly helps!');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190868263, 'Enjoyed learning the different subjects in this class and body systems.  Being pre-med it gave me a good idea of things i liked learning about and things i didn''t like learning about. Overall it was a great class.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190692833, 'Appreciated the instructors willingness to give additional help on assignments as needed.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190614241, 'It was a great course and I learned a lot. I really liked that you put up multiple ways for us to learn the information - through powerpoints, listening to class lectures, etc. That was extremely helpful to me. I think you do a fantastic job of teaching the online course. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190690823, 'I don''t really have any improvements, I have no complaints about this course');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190628686, 'I walked away with a better understanding and awareness of the ''oppressed,'' and also a realization of how easy it is to generalize and stereotype unintentionally. This class also made me think, a lot. And, while I was not necessarily a big fan of the text book, and i wish the course was a little more focused on classroom strategies for understanding and working with diverse groups, I can now understand why the course was taught the way it was. It''s really about thinking, asking questions and trying to be aware of others and their perspectives. regardless of the age we teach, an awareness and an ability to listen and try to understand others goes a long way in working with diverse populations. Thanks for an interesting course. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190880073, 'The history and theory of diversity and race were interesting to me. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190597727, 'Allowed opportunity for students to think independently.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190603729, 'I loved the discussion time.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190880056, 'The instructor encouraged group work and group collaboration. He encouraged us to express our opinions.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190628669, 'at the beginning of the course, we all read our chapter reflections out loud to the class. I really liked this. I liked hearing everyones viewpoints and what they felt was important. I wish we had done this more. I think this and the other group work, helped everyone get to know others in teh class and I liked all the variety in sharing.  ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190546478, 'Clarity on assignments.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190554558, 'Was flexible enough to allow for students to ask question or expound on a topic of discussion.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190603730, 'I would have liked just a little more structure, with clear learning targets.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190603737, 'I really liked that the final paper was linked to our thesis topic. I feel like the work I did could be used for my thesis in the future.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190880064, 'It is obvious that the instructor has a great deal of knowledge about this subject. Some of the class discussions were interesting.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190546493, 'Very positive in class and accepting of students input.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190628677, 'I really liked all the group work we did IN class. The discussions were interesting and the activities were also interesting. There was also a lot of variety in what we did. Not always the same format, which made class unique. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190880057, 'The course was very unorganized and vague. It seemed that many of the days the instructor was unprepared. As a student this was frustrating because I never knew what to expect.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190628684, 'He was available to answer questions and was willing to work with individuals and their schedules. This was really helpful, considering it was a summer course. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190880071, 'He was very willing to discuss issues which concerned us either in class or by appointment at his office. He was very nice and tried to be encouraging. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190554559, 'Provide more time for students to talk about how the lesson topic apply to their classrooms.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190876896, 'I was hesitant taking such a heavy class online, however Dr. Skopec is so extremely organized, she made it very clear of what she expected.  She also made it possible to listen to lectures early if you were going out of town and the study guides given were extremely helpful in studying for the tests.  I was very impressed with this class and learned a lot.  This is how all online classes that are also classes taken in person should be.  ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190642039, 'Lectures need to be more focused.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190692832, 'Passing the challenging Introduction to Data Structures and Algorithms course ice cream and pizza party!!!');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190642040, 'Each lecture covered the subject matter, obviously.  However, I feel the assignments were not similar enough to the lectures.  The lectures would introduce certain data structures, then the assignments were about manipulating those data structures.  The instructor created extremely elaborate assignments filled with overly complicated code that is very difficult to understand.  Having only one other C++ programming course, I found this course almost impossible to follow and I will probably fail as a result.  As the semester comes to an end, the subject matter is only increasing in difficulty, which is standard, but I am even less prepared for the last assignment than I was for the first assignment.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190546487, 'Instead of having students read their papers, have them work in groups to discuss and possibly create something meaningful to the topic to share with the class.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190880065, 'The class hardly had any structure. It was a summer course so the Instructor was a little more laid back, but the class would have been a lot better if it were better organized and if he would have followed through with the things he said. The instructor also did not seem to be very prepared. It seems that he continuously had us discuss our reading responses and ideas in groups because he didn''t really have anything planned. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190642772, 'That I didnt take it online. I feel I would have benefited more if it took the course in class. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190698324, 'I understand that it was an accelerated summer class but it still seemed that we were swamped with a ton of information and expected to remember extremely minute details of every chapter when exams came around. However, the class in total was very fun, informational, and I still seemed to do well so I really enjoyed the class and would recommend another to do it as well.  ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190713939, 'All good.  Except the weekly quizzes suck. :)');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190877043, 'The website used for the lab was a little tricky in the beginning, and I was a little confused on the first lab, but then I was fine.  I really enjoyed the labs and also the labs I was able to do on family members.  It made me feel like I was taking the class in person.  Well organized.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190554567, 'Finalized syllabus BEFORE coming to the first day of class.  Provide rubrics or give a set of standard that assignments should meet.  Less time spent rehashing what the author said and more time should be spent on how to apply the information.  Come to class with a clear idea of what you want to accomplish in class....do not leave it up to the class to decide.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190641784, 'The teacher was awesome and did a really good job at explaining and made sure everyone understood the content of the class. He was fair at grading the homework and tests and extended due dates for homework when needed.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190644562, 'I think the professor likes this topic. The only complaint that I do have is that I am a visual learner, so online is already hard for me. The power points did help, however, She was writing things up on the board and you could hear her but were unable to see her, that was really annoying. I think what she had on the board could help us in the online class. I would much rather have to print the power point and watch her talk and see what she is writing on the board. I hope this makes sense. She is a very nice lady and does a fine job. I just think this is somewhere that could be improved for us at home.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190693707, 'Hard class but very interesting! I really enjoyed this class, the slideshow lectures helped so much with this course and I wish more professors would do this. I Would definitely take another class from professor Skopec. Great class!   ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190717775, 'There were times, both in the lectures and in the assignments, that instructions weren''t very clear and at times a little confusing, making the assignments that much harder.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190690040, 'More consistent length of lectures/lab time.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190628670, 'It may have just been me, but diversity in relation to economics ( the text) was a bit difficult. i felt like I had to read the chapters with dictionaries and look up half of what Vavrus quoted in his book. The class discussions were really helpful in helping me better understand the points of the text. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190609930, 'No programming guidelines (like real programming). It is essentially a short internship. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190620928, 'Everything');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190670504, 'Peterson');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(191022732, 'I didn''t have to use a textbook (yay!), also the teacher was very personable and quite humorous, making class enjoyable to watch.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190628685, 'some of the expectations were a little confusing, and I think this was due to the fact that we shortened the course by a few weeks, due to teachers back to school dates. I think this rushed the course a bit for both the teacher and the students. However, I felt like he did his best under the circumstances to meet the needs of all and also be available for consultations. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190690039, 'Having the lectures recorded, the teaching style of the professor.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190690822, 'It was challenging and fun.  I learned a lot.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190692831, 'I enjoyed learning about the different sorting algorithms.  I liked listening in on the face to face classroom discussions live or later viewing the recording at my convenience.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190546494, 'Feedback on their papers would have been helpful.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190642771, 'I liked the way the professor explained things. He made a lot of things clear that weren''t clear in previous classes. His way of explaining was great. I felt very challenged and appreciate that his assignments forced me to use the debugger. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190554573, 'Dr. Garcia is approachable and easy to get along with.  He is also flexible in his structure (but almost too much).');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190642038, 'I like that the campus and online classes were combined.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190880072, 'The Instructor did not seem to be prepared for class, sometimes it almost seemed as if he was making it up as he went. I was a little bit frustrated at times because sometimes it felt like such a waste of time and money to be there. This class could have covered how to deal with diversity in our classrooms, instead we discussed the theory and history of diversity. This was interesting, but I couldn''t really see how it would help me on a day to day basis as a teacher.  ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190717774, 'This course was very difficult at times and I began to enjoy the challenge of another assignment.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190554574, 'Improve the syllabus and have it prepared PRIOR to class starting.  Know the criteria (what you will be covering, how many sessions/time the class will meet, etc) and CLEARLY state it in the syllabus.  Provide instruction or rubrics on how to complete projects.  Assign projects more than 1 day before they are required to present.  (It would have been really nice to have the article presentations assigned 1/3 to 1/2 of the way into the course. It would have allowed us more time to collaborate and prepare our presentations.)');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190641782, 'It was challenging and helped me learn to be a better programmer.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(191063697, 'Wonderful semester, the lectures provided in google chats kept the class focused throughout the whole lecture. (hard to find for programming courses) Great explanations of each assignment. ');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190632465, 'Brad is entertaining and makes the course fun.');
	
		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(190693212, 'I feel very confident in my choice of Strongly Agree on all points. Brad Peterson is a very professional, personable, and excellent teacher. Often times I feel some professors at Weber State know their material, but lack the skill-set of an educator. Brad does not have this issue. 

Through some magical means he can travel at just the correct pace through material that no one get''s left behind while at the same time providing enough challenges for those that learn quick. He will often stop, literally every 5 minutes or 2 minutes depending on the content, and ask if everyone understands the topic. He wants to make sure no one get''s left out. He understands that usually the majority of students don''t understand things the first time and the ones that do understand are the only ones that answer to say that they do. IE: He knows when your confused you often don''t speak up. He makes sure that a concept is properly understood by all. I really want to highlight the fact he really pushes concepts NOT memorization. I think this is an important way of teaching most professors miss. By teaching concepts I am now able to understand the Data Structure and Algorithm concepts well enough to write most of them without reference material. (Would need reference for some Sorting Algorithms we really didn''t cover much). Most other classes I have had to keep reference material or write some stuff afterwards just to ingrain the concepts in my head. And I have even taken CS3030.

He also is easy to reach. Add him on google+ and you''ll get him at all hours of the day. Is he even paid on his time off? I think he just loves code!

Brad also leverages common sense technologies to cater to his students convenience. Having each lecture recorded on youtube to watch over and over was an immense help to understanding the material-which in turn is the reason I have learned so much and subsequently have an almost perfect grade. Google plus is also a perfectly simple and reliable platform for remote attendance. Brad understands that stringent structures with in class hand written/typed notes is NOT how people naturally learn. If every professor had a teaching structure like Brad''s I could bet both my cats and my dog that the drop out rate of the CS department would halve in one semester.

This is not brown nosing when I say Brad Peterson is the best professor I have had at Weber State and I would seriously consider querying his methods for implementation in all classes. It is for the benefit of all students and for Weber State (in terms of keeping students in the program and increasing success rates).

 ');
	
