		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(198127040, 'Prof. Garcia lacked organization and preparation. We never got a syllabus and when we asked about it he said something about there being issues with canvas, but he never during the semester gave us a syllabus. I felt that he didn''t put much energy into the course and did as little as possible to get by. One class that was held was an "optional" day and this was the day (half way through the semester) that he informed us that we needed to do the CEL project and hours. When asked if the students that weren''t there would be informed of what was going on with this project he said that he would post it online.....he never posted it. Near the end of the semester a student asked for the handout on the CEL project and he basically said, sorry I don''t have it. He decided to make the course a hybrid course which I know was frustrating to a lot of students because they like the face to face teaching style. I was disappointed with his professionalism in regards to teaching a college course, especially one on education. It was almost like the class was, what not to do when teaching. ');
	
