		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(198138415, 'Ironically, this professor demonstrated prejudice, intolerance and/or insensitivity, often to the point of hostility, toward Caucasians, Christians, North Westerners, and his own students. He also made points about sexual preferences by demeaning other sexual preference groups - specifically, he repeatedly offended his Caucasian, Christian ("I don''t use the word so I don''t know how to spell it," says he), heterosexual majority class. This was an every-other week in which he missed the first class, rambled through much of the next class in an extemporaneous fashion, presented a highly-offensive sexually-explicit video to which he confessed not to have screened prior to class (a male student walked out and others wished they had but were afraid it would affect their grade if they did), showed up late and unprepared on a subsequent class in which he had the class reiterate their work one with another after introducing a short video in which he invited comment. It was disconcerting to witness, on many occasions, several usually well-spoken, engaged and confident students be uncomfortable and stressed, to the point of changing their facial coloring, who would not speak out in his classroom but had plenty to say in private against this professor, his methods and the class content. ');
	
