		INSERT INTO EssayResponses (questionResponseID, essayResponse)
		VALUES(203483095, 'Instead of us wasting our time answering quiz questions about the reading discuss what we learned with each other. Even though this class was online I felt like it would have been nice to have the assignments based on our discussions with others and not quiz questions. Since this class was situated and treated like an online class it needed to be set up so that I could show what I had learned in more productive ways than taking a quiz. While I did like that the quiz questions were essay based I never received any comments from the professor about my answers. I don''t even know if he read them. Also, this is suppose to be the historical foundations of education, not the politics of education. I felt like this class solely focused on the politics and while I did like the book choice from this class, it was from only one point of view that was not objective. I felt like there really was no room to discuss our different opinions about some of the issues. I felt like the theme of this class was "we need to focus on curriculum to fix the education system" and that there were no other opinions to be discussed. While I agreed with this theme most of the time I also know that it is a biased view and I know that you gain more when listening to others opinions and views. ');
	
